data.headline: Governor Gavin Newsom vetoes California's 'BitLicense' bill
data.text: California passed a bill to create a licensing regime and stablecoin conditions.

data.headline: Voyager's CFO leaves the company
data.text: The chief financial officer of bankrupt crypto lender Voyager will soon leave the company according to a Friday announcement. Voyager filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection and is selling off its assets in the process.

data.headline: Polkadot has made it possible for USDT to be minted on its blockchain
data.text: Tether, the company operating blockchain-enabled platform Tether.to that powers the largest stablecoin by market capitalization and the third largest cryptocurrency, announced today the launch of USDT on Polkadot. The launch would allow Tether to move in and out of the Polkadot network.

data.headline: Binance plans to add an opt-in button for the 1.2% LUNC burn tax
data.text: Binance CEO Changpeng Zhao (CZ) was asked if Binance was ever going to apply the 1.2% tax on Terra Luna Classic (LUNC) off-chain trades. The post Binance to add opt-in button for 1.2% LUNC burn tax on all trades appeared first on CryptoSlate.

data.headline: New orders from the IRS asks for more action on cryptocurrency traders
data.text: The United States has ordered the IRS to investigate crypto traders not paying taxes on their digital assets. The market has ballooned over the years, with more participants entering the sector across America.

data.headline: The CFTC is suing a DAO
data.text: The Commodity Futures Trading Commission filed a lawsuit against Ooki DAO, which may have a terrible impact on other decentralized financial services.

data.headline: CoinSquared and CoinSmart have announced that they are merging to expand their reach
data.text: Inditex will have more than $350 million in assets and approximately 1 million customers. Consolidation is happening as trading platforms and exchanges grapple with global competition as well as the ongoing market downturn. Recently in Canada, Kevin O'Leary-backed WonderFi rolled up crypto platforms Bitbuy and Coinberry.

data.headline: Congress asked the Department of State for information on crypto businesses
data.text: The bill mandates the Treasury and the State Departments to compile a report on how crypto impacts the effectiveness and enforcement of sanctions against Russia.

data.headline: UK retail investors have spent approximately 30 billion pounds on cryptocurrencies
data.text: Although crypto prices remain volatile, the UK government has released new data showing that citizens are pumping money into the cryptocurrency space.

data.headline: Celsius shareholders want a new legal representative
data.text: Celsius's shareholders have requested an official legal representation in the bankruptcy proceedings. The request appeared first on CryptoSlate.
